	<dd><a name="comment_936" ></a>
	<p><em><strong>square peg</strong> replies:</em> It is absolutely disgusting that people pay their taxes to fund education;  and then their children get refused entry to state-funded schools because of their religion. This isn't antagonism towards religion, its antagonism towards the government discriminating against children because of their religion (or, rather, their parents' religion).  Public money shouldn't be used for this.</p> <p>I hope you do vote. The parties  are all bad on this, but they're not all as bad as each other. The Tory's will give every parent £6,000ish to spent at whatever school that can charge less than that amount, Labour will create more state faith schools, and the LibDems are disinclined to push faith schools. </p>
	<small>
	written 16th Apr 2005 <!-- | <a
